BELLFLOWER SOLAR 1, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Bellflower Solar 1, LLC ("Bellflower") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Bellflower generating facility ("Bellflower Facility").
The Bellflower Facility is a solar generating facility located in Henry County, Indiana. The Bellflower Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by AEP Indiana Michigan Transmission Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Bellflower's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Bellflower Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Bellflower's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Bellflower shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $2,404,293.77 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $200,357.81
